body:
Tony: Tea? Not coffee?

Steve: I’m making some tea. Tea. T-E-A tea. Tea, tea, tea. I don’t like coffee, I like tea… Does drinking tea make me any less of a man than somebody who drinks coffee? I mean, is every tea-drinker in the entire history of the world gay to you? Is that it? What about the Boston Tea Party? Was that like some kind of a gay boat festival or something?

title: Mirror Image (MJ X Twin!Reader)
body:
Characters: MJ X Twin!Sister!Reader Peter Parker X Fem!Reader

Universe: Marvel, Avengers

Warnings: None

Request: I have a request: That MJ has a mirror image (AKA a twin) and that Peter sees MJ’s twin (Y/N) and mistakes her identify and leaves embrasssed after declaring she looks prettier today…After feeling embrasssed he walks into the real MJ and MJ bring the snarky person we love, explains why Peter was distracted and later on Peter realizes she has a twin Obviously the pairing is Peter Parker x Twin!reader Ily! ~ ObsessedFangirl

Your sister and you never had lessons together, and the school basically had you on opposite sides of the school during school hours. They did this due to the fact that when side by side, no one could tell you two apart, due to the fact that you were twins.

It bothered neither of you that you didn’t see each other till breaks or the end of the day, and after years of being separated, you’d started making it into a game. You would switch classes, go into classes when the other was sick and even pretended to be each other on certain days but be in the right class just to mess with the teachers. You only did this every so often each year so the schools never bothered to discipline you and let you have your fun. Your favourite game, however, was the game of on purpose avoiding each other and not acknowledged that you even had twins.  You had been doing this since the beginning of middle school and it didn’t dawn on you that this game could make people believe there either of you had no twin.

“Hey!” You heard someone call after you, turning to see a boy with brown hair rushing to meet you. You recognised him- Peter Parker, close friends with your sister. You knew this sort of stuff due to being twins and the games you played.

“Hey Peter.” You greeted. “What’s up?” You asked.

“Nothing really, just wanted to tell you I like what you’ve done with your hair.” He said, and you grinned at the compliment. “Also did you do that homework? The one for science?”

“Yeah, need my notes?” You offered, and he sheepishly nodded. You smiled, reaching in your bag and giving him your notes. “Give em back to me when you’re done okay? See you later Peter.” You waved and walked off, grinning with mischief as you scurried off.

A few hours later, Peter approached MJ, and noticed something was off, and MJ noticed his frown. “Peter what’s up?” She asked.

“You’re hair… I liked what you did with it.” He pouted. MJ was only confused for a second before she realised what had happened, and grinned.

“Got a bit messed up so I put it back to normal. Did you need me for something?” She asked.

“Uh yeah, here.” Peter handed back the notes, and MJ was tried not to laugh, taking the notes. “I would have given it back earlier but for some reason I struggled with your handwriting. I usually don’t.” MJ bit her lip and nodded. What made it even funnier for her was that she saw you now appear around the corner into view. You saw what was happening and you acted quickly, sneaking up behind Peter, and waiting. “Anyway, thanks again for letting me use your notes.”

“No problem.” You and your twin said at the same time, and Peter jumped out his skin, turning and seeing you. His eyes widened as he took a step out between you and looked back and forth, slowly realising what was going on, before he held his head, like he was in pain.

“How did I not realise you had a twin?” He mumbled quickly, making you both laugh, MJ handing you the notes.

“Don’t worry, you’re probably the first person to actually know besides teachers since we’ve been playing this game of pretending we don’t have twins since middle school.” MJ explained. He mumbled an apology to you that you shrugged off.

“Anyway, I’m going to go now before someone else realises there’s two of us.” You excused, rushing off, leaving an amused twin sister and a flustered Peter.

Hope you like it! If you have any questions, please send them in! 

*Not my gif

summary: PUNISHER SEASON 2: I really liked the Punisher in Dare Devil and in Season one, Jon Bernthal is the perfect actor for the job...
caption:
PUNISHER SEASON 2: I really liked the Punisher in Dare Devil and in Season one, Jon Bernthal is the perfect actor for the job but this season was just a bit slow and ultimately a little dull. It’s a real shame. In the first two series’ that he was in, they did the whole backstory and journey from wronged marine to man of vengeance and I really hoped this would be his decline into merciless vigilante psycho. Unfortunately, they dragged out the stuff with Russo and made it a “reasonable guy trapped in a difficult situation” , sort of thing. Like the Luke Cage series they were too long and could have been resolved in half the time, with a tighter more action filled script. The very last one minute epilogue scene does have him take on this authentic comic like role, but it just leaves you wishing this whole series would have been like this.

⭐️⭐️⭐️
